status: MARC21-007: Tape configuration of sound recording
Number of tracks on a tape.

definition (en): Half track configuration is used to permit two tracks (channels) to be recorded on one tape.
scope note (en): It is used with audio cassettes to permit monoaural recordings in two directions and with stereophonic recordings in one direction.

definition (en): Quarter track configuration is used to permit four tracks (channels) to be recorded on one tape.
scope note (en): It is used with standard audio cassettes to permit stereophonic recordings in two directions, and with quadraphonic recordings in one direction.

definition (en): Eight track configuration is used with monaural, stereophonic, and quadraphonic recordings.
Twelve track configuration is used in professional recording studios to permit separate control of various tracks which are later mixed to produce a stereophonic or quadraphonic recording.
Sixteen track configuration is used in professional recording studios to permit separate control of various tracks which are later mixed to produce a stereophonic or quadraphonic recording.
Item is not a tape or does not include a tape.
scope note (en): For example, if the item is a disc.

definition (en): Tape configuration other than half (2) track, quarter (4) track, eight track, twelve track, sixteen track.
